Nguyễn Trường Duy is an Intern Network Engineer / System Administrator with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in System Administration, Network Security, and Network Design, demonstrated through academic projects involving the configuration, deployment, and management of SharePoint Server environments, including Active Directory integration, SQL Server setup, and implementing HTTPS/SSL for secure access and backup/restore procedures. They have also designed and secured WiFi networks for SMEs using Cisco Packet Tracer, incorporating DHCP, VLAN, ACL, WLC-based WPA2/WPA3 security, and Cisco ASA firewall configurations. Furthermore, Duy has experience in web application development, utilizing MVC architecture with .NET Core and C# to build a gym management system, integrating SQL Server, Entity Framework Core, and implementing features like token-based authentication, access control, and basic SEO optimization, following Agile and Scrum methodologies.
Technically, Duy is proficient in programming languages such as C#, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS. They possess hands-on experience with frameworks and libraries including .NET core, MVC, Entity Framework Core, and Razor. Their database skills encompass SQL Server, MySQL, MongoDB, and phpMyAdmin. For DevOps and system administration, they are familiar with SharePoint Server, VMWare, Active Directory, and network protocols/technologies like DHCP, VLAN, ACL, WLC, WPA2, WPA3, Cisco ASA, and Cisco Packet Tracer. Version control and development tools include Git, GitHub, Gitlab, and Visual Studio, with an understanding of ILogger for application logging. Their domain knowledge extends to Configuration Management, Deployment strategies, CRUD operations, and ensuring secure communication via HTTPS and SSL Certificates, alongside practical skills in Debugging and Testing.